Technical Business Analyst with strong integration / information / data management skills. Reporting to the Project Manager, the successful applicant will investigate changes required to existing applications and reporting, document the same and
          amend the code as necessary.
You will produce functional / technical specifications to describe the change or data enhancement for graphical displays, downstream applications and reports that support the business’ requirements for clear, relevant and timely information. You
          will also have experience in making changes to Oracle (SQL and PL/SQL) code to enact these integration changes.
Supported by highly knowledgeable SMEs and working to tight timeframes, the ideal candidate will be self-motivated and results oriented. Communication and stakeholder skills are essential qualities for this position.
 Previous experience in supporting either energy markets systems or trading / risk / finance functions would be highly regarded but is not essential.
What we are looking for

Self-motivated, results oriented Business Analyst with strong information / data management skills;
Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills - strong yet consultative;
Able to quickly define and interpreting business requirements into workable action items;
Experience and knowledge of analytics (across commercial / contract risk);
Working knowledge of Energy Trading, Risk Management and Settlement systems (front, middle and back office) - desirable;
Oracle database experience; and
Data management / Data enterprise.

The BA would be required to:

Define high level business requirements;
Dataset definition and mapping;
Assist with System Integration Testing; and
Provide input to Data developer and data architect.

For more information please call Renee Clayton (renee.clayton@uandu.com) on 0477 778 449, quoting reference number 14335. Alternatively, to submit an application, please click below.
Please submit your resume in Word format only.

